<exercise number="35"><statement><p>If you count by even numbers, such as 6, 8, 10, et cetera, you are listing consecutive even integers.<ol label="a">
	<li>If your first even integer is <m>n</m>, what is the next even integer?</li>
	<li>What is the next even integer after that?</li>
	<li>Write a polynomial for the product of the three even integers in parts (a) and (b).</li></ol></p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><p><m>n+2</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>n+4</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>n^3+6n^2+8n</m></p></li></ol></p></answer></exercise>

